<p lang="en-US"><span style="font-size: small;">The questions of which law governs a document and where disputes relating to the document may be litigated are two distinct questions.</span></p>
<p class="western" lang="en-US"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Section 19.1</strong></span></p>
<p lang="en-US"><span style="font-size: small;">This document has been drafted to comply with English law, and the governing law provision should not be changed without obtaining expert advice from a lawyer qualified in the appropriate jurisdiction. In some circumstances the courts will apply provisions of their local law, such as local competition law or consumer protection law, irrespective of a choice of law clause.</span></p>
<p lang="en-US"><span style="font-size: small;">Which law should govern the document?</span></p>
